Karim Bouchetata, who posted the images to his Facebook page, told the Telegraph said everyone was stunned to see the snow falling.According to Live Science, the last time snow was reported in southern Algeria was on February 18, 1979. Several Saharan mountain ranges, however, receive snow on a more regular basis.Posted by Karim Bouchetata on Monday, December 19, 2016Posted by Karim Bouchetata on Monday, December 19, 2016Posted by Karim Bouchetata on Monday, December 19, 2016The Sahara is the largest hot desert spanning 9,200,000 square kilometres with temperatures which have preciously surpassed 47 C.Posted by Karim Bouchetata on Monday, December 19, 2016